:: context
You are looking at the screen of the game.

The system has loaded, but nothing has happened yet.

A quiet moment.

Then something changes.

[[Continue|anomaly]]


:: anomaly
A message appears.

Not a notification.
Not a quest.

Just a sentence.

"Are you lost, or are you looking?"

[[Look closer|contact]]


:: contact
The interface shifts slightly.
As if the system noticed you noticing it.

You are given three responses.

[[I'm looking.|choice_look]]
[[I might be lost.|choice_lost]]
[[Who asked that?|choice_challenge]]


:: choice_look
"Good," the system replies.

"Looking is the first skill."

A faint diagram appears.
It looks like a map of something.

[[Continue|artifact]]


:: choice_lost
"Then orientation comes first."

A faint diagram appears.
It looks like a map of something.

[[Continue|artifact]]


:: choice_challenge
"Good," the system replies.

"You noticed the anomaly."

A faint diagram appears.
It looks like a map of something.

[[Continue|artifact]]


:: artifact
You gained a BAR:

"Clarity begins with noticing."

[[End Encounter|END]]
